}\\cdot\\dfrac{d}{c}=\\dfrac{bd}{ac}.\n\\]\n\n\n\\textbf{(f)} Division undoes multiplication: If $a,b,c$ are three elements of\n$L$ with $a$ being invertible, then the equality $\\dfrac{c}{a}=b$ is\nequivalent to $c=ab$.\n\\end{proposition}\n"
